> Because this app currently generates tickets *completely offline* without a backend server, we have to hardcode a "Secret Key" (e.g., `MY_SUPER_SECRET_GOVT_KEY`) directly into the app's code so it can do the math to sign the JWT. 
>
> In a true production environment for the government, the app would ask a secure central server to generate the JWT, meaning the secret key never actually lives on the user's phone. For this implementation, I will hardcode a secret key so you can see exactly how the JWT generation works!

